# Architecture Overview: Intelligent System

The **Intelligent System** is a personalized AI memory and reasoning platform designed to manage WordPress content, analyze performance metrics, and generate strategic insights using a multi-layered data architecture.

## System Architecture Diagram

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Frontend (Dashboard)"
        UI[Web UI / HTML/JS]
    end

    subgraph "Backend (Flask)"
        API[Flask API - app.py]
        Pipe[Memory Pipeline - pipeline.py]
    end

    subgraph "Data Acquisition Layers"
        WP[WordPress Fetcher - content_layer.py]
        Perf[Performance Tracker - performance_layer.py]
    end

    subgraph "Memory Storage Engines"
        Chroma[ChromaDB - semantic_memory.py]
        Neo4j[(Neo4j Knowledge Graph - knowledge_graph.py)]
    end

    subgraph "Reasoning & Intelligence"
        AI[Reasoning Engine - reasoning_engine.py]
    end

    %% Flow
    UI <--> API
    API --> Pipe
    Pipe --> WP
    Pipe --> Perf
    WP --> Chroma
    WP --> Neo4j
    Perf --> Neo4j
    Perf --> Chroma
    Chroma --> AI
    Neo4j --> AI
    AI --> API
```

## Core Components

### 1. API & Orchestration
- **Flask Backend ([app.py](file:///c:/Users/haris/OneDrive/Desktop/Intelligent%20System/app.py))**: The central hub that serves the dashboard and provides REST endpoints for manual triggers and status monitoring.
- **Pipeline Orchestrator ([pipeline.py](file:///c:/Users/haris/OneDrive/Desktop/Intelligent%20System/pipeline.py))**: Manages the multi-stage ingestion process, ensuring data flows correctly from sources to storage and reasoning.

### 2. Data Acquisition Layers
- **Content Layer ([content_layer.py](file:///c:/Users/haris/OneDrive/Desktop/Intelligent%20System/content_layer.py))**: Connects to the WordPress REST API to fetch posts, cleans HTML, and structures content into memory objects.
- **Performance Layer ([performance_layer.py](file:///c:/Users/haris/OneDrive/Desktop/Intelligent%20System/performance_layer.py))**: Processes uploaded CSV files (e.g., from GSC or GA4) to extract metrics, calculate **Health Scores**, and flag **Content Decay**.

### 3. Memory Storage Engines
- **Semantic Memory ([semantic_memory.py](file:///c:/Users/haris/OneDrive/Desktop/Intelligent%20System/semantic_memory.py))**: Utilizes **ChromaDB** and **OpenAI Embeddings** to store content vectors, enabling similarity search and cluster detection.
- **Knowledge Graph ([knowledge_graph.py](file:///c:/Users/haris/OneDrive/Desktop/Intelligent%20System/knowledge_graph.py))**: Uses **Neo4j** to map relationships between articles, topics (categories/tags), and clusters, providing a structural view of the "content web".

### 4. Reasoning & Intelligence
- **Reasoning Engine ([reasoning_engine.py](file:///c:/Users/haris/OneDrive/Desktop/Intelligent%20System/reasoning_engine.py))**: Powered by **Groq (Llama 3)** and **LangChain**. It analyzes data from both ChromaDB and Neo4j to:
    - Identify decaying content.
    - Suggest specific updates and action items.
    - Reveal "weak clusters" in the topic map.
    - Recommend internal cross-linking opportunities.

## Tech Stack
| Category | Technology |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Backend** | Python, Flask |
| **Orchestration** | Custom Pipeline, Schedule |
| **Vector DB** | ChromaDB |
| **Graph DB** | Neo4j Community Edition |
| **Embeddings** | OpenAI (`text-embedding-3-small`) |
| **LLM Inference** | Groq (`llama-3.3-70b-versatile`) |
| **Frontend** | Vanilla JS, CSS, HTML |

## Data Flow
1. **Fetch**: WordPress content is pulled and converted to structured JSON.
2. **Metrics**: CSVs are uploaded; metrics are fuzzy-matched to posts to compute health scores.
3. **Embed**: Content is converted to vectors and stored in ChromaDB.
4. **Relate**: Links, categories, and clusters are projected into Neo4j.
5. **Reason**: The AI analyzes the combined memory to generate strategic reports.
